        {
          "@id": "http://lod.footlight.io/resource/67e40b7d1088030064bef5fb",
          "@type": "skos:Concept",
          "skos:prefLabel": [
            {
              "@language": "en",
              "@value": "Theatre"
            },
            {
              "@language": "fr",
              "@value": "Th\u00e9\u00e2tre"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "description": [
        {
          "@language": "en",
          "@value": "<p>From the Kwantlen First Nation village of Squa\u2019lets comes the tale of&nbsp;<em>Th\u2019owxiya</em>, an old and powerful spirit that inhabits a feast dish of tempting, beautiful foods from around the world. But beware\u2014if you steal from her, you will pay a terrible price!</p><p><br></p><p>When a hungry mouse named Kw\u2019at\u2019el steals a piece of cheese from her feast, he finds himself in a perilous situation. To appease the ogress, Kw\u2019at\u2019el must bring two children for her to eat before the second moon rises, or else Th\u2019owxiya will feast on his entire family!</p><p><br></p><p>Join Kw\u2019at\u2019el on his quest for knowledge and forgiveness, aided by two bears, a raven, and a sasquatch, as they navigate the challenges of this captivating journey. Using Masks and songs to tell this Kwanlten First Nation story of The Wild Woman of the Woods, this production teaches a vital lesson: when you take something from the earth, you must give something back.</p><p><br></p><p><em>Recommended for families and young children.</em></p>"
        },
        {
          "@language": "fr",
          "@value": "<p>C\u2019est au c\u0153ur du village de Squa\u2019lets, dans la Premi\u00e8re Nation Kwantlen, qu\u2019est n\u00e9 le conte de&nbsp;<em>Th\u2019owxiya</em>, celui d\u2019un esprit tr\u00e8s ancien dot\u00e9 de prodigieux pouvoirs qui vit entour\u00e9 de mets app\u00e9tissants du monde entier. Mais attention, toute personne surprise en train de lui voler ses victuailles en paiera le prix fort!</p><p><br></p><p>Et c\u2019est ce qui arrive \u00e0 Kw\u2019at\u2019el, une souris affam\u00e9e voleuse de fromage. Pour sortir de cette p\u00e9rilleuse situation, Kw\u2019at\u2019el doit rapporter \u00e0 l\u2019ogresse deux enfants avant le lever de la deuxi\u00e8me lune. S\u2019il \u00e9choue, toute sa famille finira en joyeux festin!</p><p><br></p><p>Avec pour compagnons de route deux ours, un corbeau et un sasquatch, Kw\u2019at\u2019el se lance alors dans une tr\u00e9pidante qu\u00eate de connaissances pour obtenir le pardon. M\u00ealant masques et chansons, cette production raconte l\u2019histoire de l\u2019ogresse des bois de la Premi\u00e8re Nation Kwantlen, mais livre aussi une le\u00e7on de vie : il faut rendre \u00e0 la terre tout ce qu\u2019on lui prend.</p><p><br></p><p><em>Recommand\u00e9 pour les familles et les jeunes enfants.</em></p>"
        }
      ],
