          "@type": "skos:Concept",
          "skos:prefLabel": [
            {
              "@language": "en",
              "@value": "Dance"
            },
            {
              "@language": "fr",
              "@value": "Danse"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "description": [
        {
          "@language": "en",
          "@value": "<p><em>Raven Mother</em> is the latest choreographic work by the Dancers of Damelahamid company, created in tribute to Margaret Harris (1931-2020), a Cree personality who had an immense impact on Indigenous performing arts. This show highlights her immense influence on the revitalization of First Nations dance, as well as her crucial role in preserving and transmitting cultural knowledge.</p><p><br></p><p>This production is the company's most ambitious to date. Raven Mother intertwines movement, song, insignia of power, sculpture, and design in an embodied narrative. The Raven totem, represented in multiple forms, symbolizes transformation, cultural strengthening, and the emergence of a new spirit.</p><p><br></p><p>A co-presentation of La Rotonde and the Grand Th\u00e9\u00e2tre de Qu\u00e9bec in collaboration with KWE! \u00c0 la rencontre des peuples autochtones.</p>"
        },
        {
          "@language": "fr",
          "@value": "<p><em>Raven Mother</em>&nbsp;est la toute nouvelle \u0153uvre chor\u00e9graphique de la compagnie Dancers of Damelahamid, cr\u00e9\u00e9e en hommage \u00e0 Margaret Harris (1931-2020), une personnalit\u00e9 crie qui a eu un immense impact dans les arts de la sc\u00e8ne autochtones. Ce spectacle met en lumi\u00e8re l'influence immense qu'elle a eue sur la revitalisation de la danse des Premi\u00e8res Nations, ainsi que son r\u00f4le crucial dans la pr\u00e9servation et la transmission du savoir culturel.</p><p><br></p><p>Cette production est la plus ambitieuse de la compagnie \u00e0 ce jour. En effet,&nbsp;<em>Raven Mother</em>&nbsp;entrem\u00eale le mouvement, le chant, les insignes de pouvoir, la sculpture et le design dans un r\u00e9cit incarn\u00e9. Le totem du Corbeau, repr\u00e9sent\u00e9 sous de multiples formes, symbolise la transformation, le renforcement de la culture et l'\u00e9mergence d'un nouvel esprit.</p><p><br></p><p><em>Une copr\u00e9sentation de La Rotonde et du Grand Th\u00e9\u00e2tre de Qu\u00e9bec en collaboration avec KWE!</em>&nbsp;<em>\u00c0 la rencontre des peuples autochtones.</em></p>"
        }
      ],
